### Latency breakdown (expected on your hardware)

| Stage | Expected Time | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| STT (Whisper base, CPU) | 0.5–1.5s | For 2–5s audio input |
| LLM inference | 1.5–4.0s | With RAG, 4-bit Qwen 1.5B |
| TTS (edge-tts) | 0.8–2.0s | Network call to Microsoft TTS |
| **Total roundtrip** | **3–7s** | Acceptable for voice demo |

### Key architecture decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **Whisper on CPU** | Saves GPU for LLM; `base` model is fast enough |
| **edge-tts** | Free, no API key, high quality, fast |
| **Tenant-specific voices** | Female voice for SIS, male voice for MFG |
| **Browser-based recording** | No native app needed for demo |
| **WAV format** | Universal, lossless, easy to process |
| **HTTP upload + JSON response** | Simpler than full WebSocket for demo |
| **WebSocket also available** | For streaming/real-time demo if needed |
| **Shorter max_new_tokens (256)** | Voice responses should be concise |
| **Session state** | Maintains conversation history across turns |
| **Base64 audio in JSON** | Avoids binary protocol complexity |

